      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2021-04-22</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-07-09T15:42:12Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>VA Quality Health Care Accountability and Transparency Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to make certain staffing and quality of care data publicly available on a specified VA website. Among other elements, the information published on the website should include statistics related to patient wait times, effectiveness of care, and staffing and vacancy information.</p> <p>The website must be (1) directly accessible from the main VA website and the main websites of each VA medical center, and (2) understandable and usable by the general public.</p> <p>The VA must implement a self-auditing process to assess the accuracy and completeness of the data available on the website.</p>]]>
          </text>
